50|$|The breech {{is opened}} by the {{breechblock}} moving in-line with {{the axis of}} the barrel and is locked in the closed position by an obstruction such as a <b>cam,</b> <b>wedge,</b> paw or over-centre levers. A roller lock is commonly associated with firarms produced by Heckler & Koch. This type of breechblock {{can be adapted to}} cycle by lever, cocking handle or gas. The mechanism is usually designs so that a single action unlocks and then withdraws the breechblock using either a slide or levers.|$|E

